            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="2.349" end="x">[In English] France, September the 12th, 1946, at <a class="placename" href="#vothL19">HÃ©nonville</a>, about fifty kilometers from <a class="placename" href="#vothL13">Paris</a>. A <a class="term" href="#vothG_kibbutz">Kibbutz</a> in a wonderful countryside, in an old castle, for displaced Jews. The interviewee is Mrs. Clara Neiman, a woman who was converted, I understand, to Judaism. And so, Mrs. Neiman.</span>
        </li>
